SIMPLE: marron
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marron
<hw>Mar*ron"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Maroon</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A large chestnut.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A chestnut color; maroon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Pyrotechny & Mil.)</fld> <def>A paper or pasteboard
box or shell, wound about with strong twine, filled with an explosive,
and ignited with a fuse, -- used to make a noise like a cannon.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>maroon</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marroon</ent>⟦br⟧
